dded, inclining tableward a translucent shoulder restrained by a black ribbonlike strap, “Not counting, of course, a half-dozen little old ladies, and that character over there with the turned-around collar.”

Kern replied, “You’re mistaken. I have no homeland. It’s true I spent many years in London. Besides—”

